node.text:
Chicken Pasta Salad and a chance to win a $250 WALMART gift card! #ad 

I’ve teamed up with @walmart and @worldfoodchampionships to create this chicken pasta bowl. Join in on the fun and enter for a chance to win! Get your inspiration on www.walmart.com/cookingchallenge to learn more about the rules and post your creation on FB and instagram using the hashtag #walmartcookingchallenge. Good luck! 

Chicken Pasta Salad Recipe 
Serve 4 

* 2 Boneless Skinless Chicken Breasts, diced 
* 1 Tbsp Olive Oil
* 1 tbsp lemon pepper 
* 1 tsp salt 
* 8 oz whole grain pasta, or gluten-free
* 1 Cup Cherry Tomatoes halved
* 1/4 cup corn 
* 1/4 cup shredded cheese 
* 1/4 Cup Green Olives sliced in half
* 2 cups fresh chopped spinach 

Dressing:
* 2 Tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil
* 2 Tbsp White Wine Vinegar
* 1 tbsp Honey
* 1 tbsp oregano 
* 2 tsp thyme 
* 1 Garlic Cloves pressed or minced
* 1 tsp salt 
* 1/2 tsp pepper 

Directions 
1-  Sauté the diced chicken with olive oil, lemon pepper and salt. Set aside 
2- Cook pasta according to package directions 
3- Meanwhile, chop and setup the other ingredients and make the salad dressing. 
4- Add everything in a large bowl and too with the salad dressing and mix well. 
5- Serve and enjoy!
.
Link in my profile for more details 
https://bit.ly/37IwwPL

node.text:
I love Salads 😍😩 This Roasted Chickpea and avocado salad is a great way to use up your veggies and enjoy a great-tasting salad loaded with fiber. Easy to make salad recipe with a homemade Greek yogurt dressing that’s simple and delicious.
.
Click the link in my profile for the recipe
https://healthyfitnessmeals.com/roasted-chickpea-avocado-salad/

node.text:
This Baked Honey Mustard Salmon recipe is so easy to make and ready to serve in just under 30 minutes. This salmon filet recipe is so healthy, moist, delicious, and oven-baked to perfection. Perfect for a busy weeknight dinner.
.
Click the link in my profile for the recipe
https://healthyfitnessmeals.com/baked-honey-mustard-salmon/

node.text:
Baked Feta Pasta may have been viral and trending a few months ago but would be a quick and easy dish to whip up for your cookout today!
.

Click the link in my profile for the recipe
https://healthyfitnessmeals.com/baked-tomato-feta-pasta/

node.text:
This Healthy Mustard Potato Salad recipe has all the flavors of classic potato salad, but with Greek yogurt instead of mayo.
.
Click the link in my profile for the recipe
https://healthyfitnessmeals.com/easy-mustard-potato-salad/

node.text:
These tasty Banana Oatmeal Pancakes are sweet, incredibly fluffy, and the perfect recipe for breakfast or brunch! Made with bananas, oat flour, and spices, this recipe is exactly what you need for the perfect banana oat pancakes.
.
Click the link in my profile for the recipe
https://healthyfitnessmeals.com/banana-oatmeal-pancakes/

node.text:
Simple, fresh, and delicious, this Grilled Cilantro Lime Chicken packs a zesty punch! Boneless skinless chicken breasts are covered in a light and flavorful herby marinade, with garlic, fresh cilantro, and lime.
.
Click the link in my profile for the recipe
https://healthyfitnessmeals.com/cilantro-lime-chicken/

node.text:
Find it hard to make steel cut oats!? Dont! Make this peanut butter banana steel cut oats recipe this weekend. They are easy to make, super creamy, and a whole lot more filling and nutritious 😍
.

Click the link in my profile for the recipe
https://healthyfitnessmeals.com/steel-cut-oats/

node.text:
Creamy Chicken Stew
.

Ingredients
1 1/2 lb chicken breast diced
1 tsp Italian seasoning
2 tbsp olive oil
2 large carrots diced
1 small onion
2 stalks celery diced
3 tbsp gluten-free flour
A few sprigs of fresh rosemary thyme, and sage
Kosher salt and pepper to taste
1 ½ cups potatoes peeled and diced
1 ½ cups sweet potatoes peeled and diced
1 red bell pepper finely diced
3 cups chicken broth or chicken stock
1 cup frozen peas
4 oz cream cheese
.

https://healthyfitnessmeals.com/chicken-stew/

.

Salmon Florentine
.
Ingredients
4-5 Salmon Fillets skin on
2 Tbsp Olive Oil divided
3 Large Garlic Cloves pressed
5 oz Fresh Spinach roughly chopped, about ¾ Cup
6 oz Button Mushrooms sliced, ¾ cup
¼ Cup Vegetable Broth
¾ Cup Coconut Cream
Kosher salt and pepper, to taste
.

https://healthyfitnessmeals.com/easy-salmon-florentine/
